the American Indian tribes and early settlers for its 
medicinal value. Although the preparation of this 
species and the ailments it treats vary somewhat 
among the tribes, rhizomes are the most commonly 
used part.  
Wildlife  Sweet flag provides habitat for waterfowl.  
Muskrats eat the rhizomes and wood ducks consume 
the seed. 
 
