better growth.  The seed germinates rapidly, and 
streambanks underneath mature trees are often 
covered with seedlings shortly after seed dispersal in 
the late spring, especially along the waterline.  The 
rapid growth means that seedlings are almost always 
out-planted as 1-0 stock. 
