native, annual to short-lived perennial plant that 
could be classified as a forb or subshrub growing 3 to 
6 feet tall.  The stems are well-branched and 
moderately leafy.  The leaves are compound, have 25 
to 60 leaflets measuring 3 inches long, and are 
sensitive to light and touch.  The flowers are yellow 
