UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_Uses='Grazing/rangeland/hayland: Crested wheatgrass is 
commonly recommended for forage production.  It is 
palatable to all classes of livestock and wildlife and is 
a desirable feed in spring and also in the fall if it re-
grows enough.  It is commonly utilized for winter 
forage by cattle and horses, but protein supplements 
are required to ensure good animal health.  It can 
withstand very heavy grazing pressure (65% use and 
greater) once stands are established.  The best forage 
types in order are Siberian, desertorum, and Hycrest.  
The cristatum type is not considered a productive 
forage type.  
 
