used on roadsides.  Ephraim  (Turkey) is rhizomatous 
when planted in higher precipitation zones above 14 
inches, and is useful for disturbed areas, mine spoils, 
roadsides and turf applications.  Parkway  is 
recommended for hay and pasture. and  Ruff  is 
recommended for a short season spring forage crop, 
roadsides, parks, and playgrounds in low rainfall 
areas of the central Great Plains. 
' WHERE symbol='agcr';
