spring or late summer.  Seeding depth is 1/4 inch.  
Redtop is seldom seeded alone, except for temporary 
cover.  Rates of seeding will vary depending upon 
purpose, and whether seeded alone or in mixtures. In 
mixtures, rates of 1 to 2 pounds per acre are generally 
used.  For pure stands, seeding rates are from 4 to 5 
pounds per acre.  The higher rates are used for 
temporary critical area stabilization.  Redtop grows 
rapidly after seeding and excessive seeding rates are 
not recommended, particularly in mixtures.  When 
used for erosion control on critical areas, fertilizing is 
essential to give rapid cover. 
 
