serviceberry (2-year-old stock) should be planted on 
the upper bank.  Weed control and supplemental 
irrigation during the first growing season enhance 
survival and growth.  Moderate browsing can 
increase twig production.  Spring burns on high 
elevation rangeland can cause mortality but also 
significantly increase twig production in Pacific 
serviceberry. 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
