serotinum) is a common pest in the South.  Minor 
problems with leaf miner and iron chlorosis which 
commonly occurs when grown on calcareous soils 
and other high pH soils.  River birch has no serious 
insect pests and is considered borer resistant.  The 
tree is not very vulnerable to deer browsing. 
