UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_Uses='Grazing/rangeland/hayland: Prairie sandreed is a 
native, sod forming, warm-season grass commonly 
found on sandy rangeland sites throughout the 
Central and Northern Plains. This grass species is 
considered a key species in grazing programs because 
of its abundance, yield potential and distribution of 
forage production during the growing season. Prairie 
sandreed begins growth earlier in the spring than 
most other warm-season grass species, thus it 
provides forage for early livestock grazing. 
 
' WHERE symbol='calo';
