just prior to planting.  The sweating procedure 
involves placing the seedlings in moist sand or peat 
moss and covering with plastic.  Conservation grade 
stock can be either 1 or 2 years old and 12 to 24 
inches tall, with a caliper of 3/16 to 1/2 inch. 
