Manhattan, Kansas 
 
Recreation and beautification: The flowers of this 
plant can be used to beautify areas where wildflowers 
are planted.  Partridge pea is commonly grown as an 
ornamental.  The bright yellow flowers make it a 
popular choice for use in native gardens.   
 
Livestock Caution: Although partridge pea foliage is 
nutritious, it can be poisonous and should be 
considered potentially dangerous to cattle. 
 
' WHERE symbol='chfa2';
