spreading, short, and somewhat tufted.  The narrow 
leaf blades are hairless, rough on the edges, slightly 
in-rolled, 0.5 to 1.5 (2) mm wide, and 1 to 10 cm 
long.  Flower heads (panicles) are open, 7 to 25 cm 
long, with ascending lower branches.  Annual 
hairgrass occurs from near sea level at the coast to 
8000 feet in the Rocky Mountains.  It is primarily 
