ALTER TABLE usda_plants ADD fs_ TEXT;
UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_='Establishment 
Annual hairgrass germinates readily and is easy to 
establish on open, moist ground.  There is no seed 
dormancy and therefore no requirement for 
physiological conditioning or over wintering 
outdoors.  However, as a winter annual in milder 
growing climes of the West Coast, it is best suited to 
early fall sowing.  The seed should be run through a 
debearder or brush machine to remove pubescence 
(hairs).  This will accentuate further seed cleaning 
and improve flow through a drill and other planting 
device.  There are approximately 900,000 seeds per 
pound (+/- 30%).  A seeding rate of 1 lb/acre pure 
live seed (PLS) would result in 20 live seeds per 
square foot.  Seeding rates will vary widely 
depending on planting purpose, site conditions, and 
method used. 
 
 
 
