UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_='Uses 
Ethnobotanic:  Eastern purple coneflower was one of 
the most important medicinal plants used by Native 
Americans.  It was used by many tribes throughout 
North America to treat a variety of ailments.  It was 
used as a pain reliever, anti inflammatory, a treatment 
for toothaches, coughs, colds, and sore throats.  It 
was also used as an antidote for various forms of 
poisonings, including snake bite.   Portions of this 
plant were used to dress wounds and treat infections.  
