UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_='Uses:  Roemer’s fescue is an important native grass 
for restoration of upland prairie and oak savanna 
within its natural range of western Oregon, western 
Washington, and northwest California.  While 
uncommon or even rare due to habitat loss, it is still 
dominant in some remnant prairies.  Typically found 
on steep, shallow, or highly mineral soils, it may also 
be useful for revegetation and erosion control where 
a slower establishing, fine textured native grass is 
desired.  Although Roemer’s fescue does not 
Plant Materials &lt.http://plant-materials.nrcs.usda.gov/&gt. 
