moving down to New England, across the Great 
Lakes region and the upper Midwest to Oregon, and 
into the Southwest.  Sweetgrass usually inhabits 
moist ground on shores (fresh or brackish), meadows, 
low prairies, at the edges of woods, bogs and 
marshes.  Normally, it is not found in pure stands but 
 
 
 
