UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_Uses='The dense stands that soft rush form have deep 
fibrous root systems, which provide very good 
shoreline protection, filter suspended solids, up-take 
nutrients, and facilitate substrate oxidation. With its 
low pH and metal tolerances, soft rush often survives 
polluted conditions. The seed and vegetative parts of 
soft rush are utilized by waterfowl, muskrats, non-
game birds, moose and domestic livestock for food or 
cover. The stems of this grass-like plant have been 
traditionally used for making floor mats, and chair 
seats. 
