UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_Cultivars_Improved_andSelectedMaterials_and='area of origin) 
Two cultivars of shrub lespedeza have been 
developed and released to the commercial market by 
the USDA-Natural Resources Conservation Service.  
‘VA-70’ (Manchuria, China) was selected for its 
wildlife value and cold hardiness by the Cape May 
Plant Materials Center, Cape May Court House, NJ.  
‘Amquail’ (Japan) was developed at Americus, GA  
 
 





