star, Kansas blazing star, button snakeroot, starwort 
 
' WHERE symbol='lipu';
ALTER TABLE usda_plants ADD fs_Uses TEXT;
UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_Uses='Forage: Dotted gayfeather is a forage or a browse 
species that is consumed by sheep and also wildlife 
species such as deer and antelope. Its forage quality 
is rated as fair to good and it will decrease under 
continuous heavy grazing. 
  
Ethnobotanical: American Indian tribes used dotted 
gayfeather for both food and medicinal purposes. The 
Kiowa gathered the roots in the spring when they 
were sweet and baked them over a fire. Gayfeather 
roots were said to vary greatly in palatability 
