Three-flower melic is a member of the Festuceae 
tribe of the grass family (Poaceae).  Gould (1975) 
notes that the common name three-flower melic is 
inappropriate for most Texas accessions because the 
plants’ spikelets commonly have only two perfect 
florets. 
 
