Oklahoma, and Texas.  In Texas, it is most often 
found in the Edwards Plateau and the North Central 
regions, but can also be found west to the Trans-
Pecos and East to the western portion of East Texas.  
It is usually found in open woods, on moist canyon 
slopes, in canyon bottoms, on rocky grasslands, as 
well as along stream banks and along roadsides.  
Three-flower melic tends to prefer partial shade, and 
calcareous or sandy loam soils. 
 
