‘Wildwood’ (NJ and NC).  This cultivar was 
developed and released by the Cape May PMC in 
1992.  It is the product of open crossing of four 
native selections of the mid-Atlantic region.  
Foundation seed and breeders stock plants can be 
obtained by nurseries from the Cape May PMC, in 
Cape May Court House, NJ.  Planting stock of 
‘Wildwood’ and common bayberry can be obtained 
through numerous native plant nurseries. 
