Seeds are drilled at the rate of 15 per foot of row and 
covered with ½ - 1 inch of soil.  A mulch of pine 
needles is recommended.  Beds must be kept moist. 
It sprouts from the stump following disturbance. 
Sprouts arise from suppressed buds and are 
