be planted ¼ inch deep.  A seeder with a legume box 
works well in the seeding operation, although other 
types of seeders or drills may be used.  Stiff 
goldenrod is easily propagated from seed.  Seed sown 
in spring will produce transplants in one season.  For 
permanent plantings, use transplants in fall or spring.  
Plants are largely cross-pollinated. 
