UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_Management='Maidencane will respond favorably to fertilization, 
though it is typically not needed for conservation 
purposes.  Fertilization may aid in establishment of 
new plantings or when used as a forage.  Proper 
grazing management is necessary due to its high 
palatability and intolerance of heavy grazing.  No 
more than 50% of its biomass should be removed 
each year from grazing or cutting to maintain healthy, 
vigorous stands.     
 
