Establishment 
Plants can be established by seed or seedlings.  Seed 
should be drilled into a firm, weed-free seed bed in the 
fall at a rate of 1.65 kg PLS/ha (1.5 lb PLS/ac).  If the 
seed is planted in a mix, the seeding rate should be 
adjusted according to the proportion of P. attenuatus in 
the mix. The drill should be set no deeper than 0.3 cm 
(1/8 in) or the seed should be placed in a separate drill 
box (with other small-seeded species) and the tubes for 
this box should be pulled so the seed is dropped on the 
soil surface.  Drag chains or press wheels should be used 
as long as the seed is not covered with more than 0.3 cm 
(1/8 in) of soil.  The seed can also be broadcast onto the 
soil surface with a broadcast spreader, and pressed into 
