UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_AdaptationandDistribution='Timothy is adapted to a cool and humid climate.  
Timothy thrives best on rich, moist bottomlands and 
on finer textured soils, such as clay loams.  It does 
not do well on coarser soils.  It prefers a pH of 5.5 to 
7.0.  Timothy will grow for a time on soils low in 
fertility, but it is better adapted to a high fertility soil.  
It is not well adapted to wet, flat land where water 
stands for any considerable time, though it can 
withstand somewhat poorly-drained soils.  Under 
limited moisture conditions, it makes a poor recovery 
and it does not tolerate drought or prolonged high 
temperatures. 
 
