Vegetative propagation is usually done by grafting.  
If grass-stage seedlings are top-killed, they can sprout 
from the root collar. Once height growth begins, 
sprouting ability decreases rapidly. 
Heavy grazing can reduce tree density, significantly 
reducing establishment and causing crop failure. 
