for 2 to 3 years and directly planted into the field, or 
they may be transplanted after the second year and 
left in a transplant bed for 1 or 2 years before field 
plantings.  This will produce a seedling 
approximately 12 to 16 inches in height with 1/4 to 
1/2 inch caliper.  Field establishment of seedlings is 
accomplished with tree planting procedures, using 
machine transplanters or hand planting. 
 
 
 
