establishment.  It is desirable to dig a hole 2-3 times 
larger than the container, backfill with peat moss, 
then mix thoroughly with the sand.  Place the roots in 
the hole and backfill around them.  Water 
immediately. Japanese black pine is grown in 
nurseries from seed, using conventional propagation 
practices. 
