surface at a rate of 2 pounds per acre and pressed in with 
a roller or harrow.  Best germination occurs at cool 
temperatures after fall rains begin, usually within one to 
two weeks.  There are approximately 1.3 million seeds 
per pound, resulting in about 30 live seeds per square foot 
for each pound of pure live seed that is planted.  Plants 
can also be started as plugs in a greenhouse set at 
moderate temperatures (70°F days/50°F nights).  The 
plugs should be planted out in the early spring at a 
spacing of 3 to 9 inches. 
