and Utah Division of Wildlife Resources, Ephraim, 
Utah. Seven other agencies in California, Idaho, 
Nevada, and Oregon cooperated. Its origin is near 
Janesville in Lassen County, California. 
 
Fountain Green germplasm is a source identified 
release of antelope bitterbrush. It was released in 
1990 by the USDA Forest Service, Shrub Sciences 
Laboratory, Provo, Utah, and the Utah Division of 
Wildlife Resources, Ephraim, Utah. Its origin is 
North of Fountain Green, Utah. 
 
Maybell germplasm was released in 1997 as a 
selected class release by Upper Colorado 
Environmental Plant Center. Five other agencies 
participated in the release.  Maybell’s origin is 
Moffat County in Northwest Colorado, near the town 
of Maybell.  
