Willow oak is a medium to large-sized tree that 
grows up to over 100 feet tall, with a trunk 3 to 6 feet 
in diameter.  It has thick, smooth, light-reddish bark 
when young. which becomes roughened and divided 
into narrow ridges on older trees.  The leaves are 
simple, alternate, deciduous, elongated and slender, 
with smooth edges. they are light green and shiny 
above, dull and paler below with distinct venation.  
The small, round, brown acorns are usually produced 
singly or in pairs with a shallow, saucer-shaped cap.  
The overlapping scales that make up the cap are thin, 
hairy, and dark red.  There are about 462 acorns per 
pound. 
