UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_='Establishment 
Stands of this species can be readily established from 
seed.  Plantings can be made in either the spring or 
fall.  Spring plantings may require the seed to be 
stored slightly above freezing for at least 30 days to 
ensure good germination.  The seed requires a clean, 
firm seed bed, and may be drilled or broadcast.  
