UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_='Establishment 
A clean, firm seedbed is essential.  The site should be 
treated with a herbicide to control vegetation, tilled, 
culti-packed once or twice, and allowed to settle 
thoroughly before sowing. 
 
Broadcast 0.5-1 gram seed per 100 square feet (0.5-1 
lb/acre).  The seed can be mixed with sand or rice 
hulls to increase volume so that it will be easier to 
spread uniformly over the planting site.  The seed 
must remain on the soil surface because it is easily 
smothered when buried in the soil.  Heavy rains after 
planting may cause the seed to be buried or washed 
from the site. 
