long-lived woody perennial hardy to -4°F. It prefers 
sun or partial shade and well-drained, moderately 
fertile soil of near neutral or slightly acidic pH. Plants 
are commonly found from southwest British 
Columbia through western Washington and Oregon 
(mostly west of the Cascade Mountains crest) and the 
California Coast Ranges to Santa Barbara County. 
There are also small relict populations in northern 
Idaho.' WHERE symbol='risa';
