UPDATE usda_plants SET fs_='Establishment 
Black-eyed Susan is easily established with most 
critical area seeding techniques.  Generally ½ lb. of 
seed per acre is sufficient in mixes with conservation 
grasses, legumes, and other forbs.  Where the intent 
is to maximize the impact of the forb component, 
utilize bunchgrasses rather than aggressively 
spreading grasses such as reed canarygrass or 
bromegrass.  Once established, new seedlings will be 
produced from the preceding crop. the stand may 
perpetuate itself indefinitely. 
 
' WHERE symbol='ruhi2';
