cover for small birds. During summer, the partial 
shade under American elder promotes a dense ground 
cover of grasses and forbs that offers good loafing or 
feeding areas for broods of young pheasants and 
quail. 
American elder can be used for erosion control on 
moist sites.  It pioneers on some strip-mine spoils and 
may occasionally be useful for reclamation planting.  
It is very decorative when in bloom. elder flowers 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
