Pests and Potential Problems  
None Known  
  
Environmental Concerns  
None Known  
  
Cultivars, Improved, and Selected Materials (and area 
of origin)  
Duck creek germplasm was released from the James E. 
“Bud” Smith Plant Materials Center, Knox City, TX in 
2000.  The germplasm was originally collected in 1982 
from native plants located along an intermittent stream 
flowing into Duck Creek north of Spur in Dickens 
County, Texas. The potential use of Duck Creek 
Germplasm is for range seeding and revegetation on 
disturbed or damaged sites that have saline problems.  
 
  
