production, exclude livestock or do not cut for hay 
after May 1.  For reseeding, allow plants to attain a 
minimum height of 12 to 15 inches in early July to 
mature seed.  For hay, cut in early bloom stage.  
When ‘Meechee’ arrowleaf clover is grown with 
summer perennial grasses, graze or cut surplus 
growth of grass to 2 inches by October 1.  
 
 
 
 
 
